# PR Files & Lint




Lists all files changed in the current branch vs main and runs ktfmt and clang linter.




---




## Step 1: Get Changed Files




Run this command to get all changed files:




```bash
git diff --name-only main...HEAD
```




## Step 2: Classify Each File




For each file, determine if it's NEW or MODIFIED:




```bash
git show main:<filepath> 2>/dev/null && echo "MODIFIED" || echo "NEW"
```




## Step 3: Print File Table




Output a table like this:




```
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
📋 FILES CHANGED (branch vs main)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════




| # | File | Status |
|---|------|--------|
| 1 | src/main/kotlin/.../MyFile.kt | 🆕 NEW |
| 2 | src/main/kotlin/.../OtherFile.kt | ✏️ MODIFIED |
| 3 | src/test/kotlin/.../MyFileTest.kt | 🆕 NEW |




Total: X files (Y new, Z modified)
```




## Step 4: Run ktfmt Linter




For all `.kt` files in the list, run ktfmt with google-style:




```bash
# Download ktfmt if not present
if [ ! -f /tmp/ktfmt.jar ]; then
curl -L -o /tmp/ktfmt.jar https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/facebook/ktfmt/0.44/ktfmt-0.44-jar-with-dependencies.jar
fi




# Run ktfmt on changed Kotlin files
git diff --name-only main...HEAD | grep '\.kt$' | xargs -r java -jar /tmp/ktfmt.jar --google-style
```


## Step 5: Run clang Linter




For all `.proto` files in the list, run clang-format with google-style (-i --style=Google):


Download clang-format if not present
```bash
# Run clang-format on changed Proto files
git diff --name-only main...HEAD | grep '\.proto$' | xargs -r clang-format -i --style=Google "$@"
```


### Step 6: Run buildifier


For all bazel build files in the list, run buildifier
Download buildifier if not present
```go install github.com/bazelbuild/buildtools/buildifier@latest
# Run buildifier on all the changed build files
```
## Step 7: Print Linting Summary




```
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
🎨 LINTING COMPLETE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════




Files formatted: X
```




If ktfmt made changes, list which files were modified.




---




## Output Format




The complete output should be:




1. File table (Step 3)
2. Linting summary (Step 5)




That's it. This rule does NOT analyze code quality - use other rules for that.











